rComments: Great human. Goes over the main concepts several times to make sure his students understand the important aspects of the content. Very kind and sweet and really cares about his students. Doesn't make you feel bad for not knowing things you "should already know."

Thorough, thoughtful, deeply knowledgeable. Lectures can be very dry and conventional. One-on-one, he has a lovely sense of humour and reflection, but this does not show in front of a large group. Very, very bright person with deep commitment to the law.

Professor Chen is extremely knowledgable and can typically answer any question that comes his way. However, his accent combined with the fast pace of his talking makes lectures hard to follow. Readings are light, but you have to really pay attention in lecture. The final was graded very inconsistently upon review and discussion with other classmate
